        <h2>Why Mumbai Basements Are at High Risk</h2>
        <p>In a city that experiences over 2,000mm of annual rainfall, basement seepage isn’t just a nuisance—it’s a structural emergency. Between the high water table in <strong>South Mumbai</strong> and the intense hydrostatic pressure in <strong>Andheri or Bandra</strong>, your foundation needs more than just paint.</p>
        
        <div class="highlight-box">
            <strong>The Cost of Neglect:</strong> Continuous moisture leads to "concrete cancer" (carbonation), rusting the TMT bars inside your structure and significantly reducing property value.
